canonical:
  title: 高亭山
  author: 李齊賢
  language: lzh
  text: 江上山如淡掃眉人家處處槿花籬停舟欲問松間寺策杖先窺竹下池帆影暮連芳草遠鍾聲曉出白雲遲憑欄一望三吳小像想將軍立馬時
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 高亭山
  author: 李齊賢
  language: lzh
  text: 江上山如淡掃眉。人家處處槿花籬。停舟欲問松間寺。策杖先窺竹下池。帆影暮連芳草遠。鍾聲曉出白雲遲。憑欄一望三吳小。像想將軍立馬時。
korean:
  title: 고정산
  author: 이제현
  language: kor
  text: |-
    강녘의 산들은 아미를 엷게 단장한 듯
    인가 울타리엔 무궁화가 곳곳에 피었네
    배 멈추고 송림 속의 절 어딘지 묻다가
    지팡이 짚고 대 아래 못 먼저 엿보네
    돛 그림자는 황혼에 멀리 초원을 이었고
    종소리는 새벽에 천천히 구름에서 나오누나
    난간에서 바라보니 삼오가 손바닥만
    장군이 말 세웠던 때를 상상하여 보노라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0180_010_0480&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 고정산(高亭山) : '
    value: “백운(伯韻) 승상(丞相)이 군사를 주둔했던 곳.”이라는 제주(題註)가 있다.
english:
  title: Mount Gaotingshan
  author: Lee Jehyeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Mountains along the river, delicate as eyebrows lightly brushed.
    Every household's fence adorned with hibiscus blooms.
    I halt the boat to ask where the temple hides among the pines,
    And leaning on my staff, first glimpse the pool beneath the bamboo.

    The sail's shadow stretches with the dusk across distant meadows,
    While the bell's voice drifts slowly from the clouds at dawn.
    Leaning on the railing, I survey the world grown small as my palm,
    And in my mind's eye see the general standing firm upon his steed.
  footnotes:
    - Gaotingshan was a place where Bakyun, the Prime Minister, once stationed his troops, lending this landscape a historical resonance that deepens the speaker's meditation on past glory.
